{
  "message": "fuzz(dir-operations): fix duplicate-name oracle + 25 structured seeds\n\nThe harness's \"removing the same name twice should fail\" assertion\nwas unconditional, but ext4's add_entry permits duplicate basenames\n(a directory can hold multiple entries sharing a name with different\ninodes). On any input that produces duplicate names \u2014 the empty\ninput is the trivial case, where every entry defaults to \"a\" with\nino 10..21 \u2014 the second remove finds the next duplicate and reports\nok:true, tripping a spurious abort.\n\nFix: count name occurrences in the model and assert ok:true when\nduplicates exist, ok:false when unique.\n\nAdd 25 structured seeds spanning the harness's input matrix:\n  * each block size (64/128/256/512/1024)\n  * reserved_tail = 0 vs 12 (parity branch)\n  * hash versions 0..4\n  * single-char / max-length (24-char) / varying-length names\n  * homogeneous file-type pools (all reg / all dir / all symlinks)\n  * mixed file-type entry sets\n  * non-zero hash seed (4\u00d7u32)\n  * potential hash-collision name set (similar prefixes)\n  * mutation counts 0 / 1 / 12 (header) / 16 (scattered) / 32 (max)\n  * probe & remove indices targeting middle entries\n  * largest block \u00d7 max entries (12)\n  * smallest block where one entry won't fit\n  * random-target name fully consumed from cursor\n\n343K runs / 11s post-fix surface no crashes.",
